stimulus:
Hello, and welcome to our study!

In this study, we will show you 30 simple statements.

We need your help deciding whether some things are probable, improbable, impossible, or nonsense.

Probable means it is something that is likely to happen.

  • For example, "I painted the house with my brush."

Improbable means it is something that is possible, but unlikely.

  • For example, "I painted the house with my hair."

Impossible means it is something that cannot happen in our world given the laws of nature.

  • For example, "I painted the house with my mind."

Nonsense means it is something that does not make any sense due to some basic conceptual or structural error.

  • For example, "I painted the house with my number."

You are going to be given 30 statements. Please categorize them into one of the four categories above.

Once you are done reading, please press SPACEBAR to continue.

We are almost ready for the study. Before we start, we have a few comprehension questions, to make sure you understand the task.

You will see a few statements and be asked to categorize them into one of the four categories of probable, improbable, impossible and nonsense.

You must correctly categorize all of the statements to move onto the experiment!

Please press the "1" key for Probable, the "2" key for Improbable, the "9" key for Impossible and the "0" key for Nonsense.



Press SPACEBAR to begin.
Finding an alligator under your bed.
Pouring yourself a glass of honey.
Painting the clouds in the sky pink.
Locking a door with a day.

Congratulations, you passed the comprehension check! Now we will move onto the experiment.

Probable means it is something that is likely to happen.

  • For example, "I painted the house with my brush."

Improbable means it is something that is possible, but unlikely.

  • For example, "I painted the house with my hair."

Impossible means it is something that cannot happen in our world given the laws of nature.

  • For example, "I painted the house with my mind."

Nonsense means it is something that does not make any sense due to some basic conceptual or structural error.

  • For example, "I painted the house with my number."

For the trials, we will show you one sentence at a time. Please try to categorize the sentence as quickly as you can.
